data.description: Charming fixer-upper opportunity! This historic home, built in 1900, boasts original trim on the first level and hardwood floors. With approximately 1200 square feet of living space, this cozy home offers character and potential.  The bathroom has been updated in the recent years. The seller had taken down the wall seperating the original 2 front bedrooms, but never was able to finish the room. The future owner can finish the remodel or change it back to the original 3 bedrooms.  Outside, a fenced-in yard provides privacy and security, ideal for pets or outdoor gatherings. The property's proximity to downtown and Bay City's St. Patrick's Day parade ensures convenience and excitement year-round.  Although the garage needs to be torn down, the basement is wired for 220, offering possibilities for workshop space or additional utilities. The roof was redone in 2009, newer hot water heater and cute porch for added curb appeal.  Don't miss this opportunity to customize and restore this vintage gem to its full potential! With its prime location and historic charm, it's sure to be a cherished home for years to come.
